How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
5 out of 5 stars

Nice heavy Fall/Winter weight shirt, great for layering.

We ordered the 2X (my husband is 6"/275lbs) and it's a nice loose comfy fit that will easily accommodate layering. This could also be worn open or even as a jacket. The blue is a royal blue (my pics don't do the color justice :( The fabric is thick and there is a subtle vertical texture and just a bit of a sheen. The shirt can be worn tucked or untucked and is very well constructed. Great shirt!

The Tobeman
5.0 out of 5 stars Fits and Looks Great and Super Comfortable
Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2024
Color: Navy BlueSize: X-LargeVine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
Love the way this shirt fits even my dad bod. It's roomy enough for a bit of a belly, and the material, which is polyester and Spandex, is really comfortable. It's a heavy shirt though, but since it's long sleeve, I won't be wearing it in the summer anyway, but it will be great for Fall and Winter. It's not a "hot" shirt, if you know what I mean. Some shirts are really hot the moment you put them on. This is not like that, but the material is thicker.
The shirt hangs really nicely, and it looks great untucked. I don't look like the models on their Amazon page, but it still looks really good on me. Sizing was true to what I normally get. I'm ready to put this into my Fall wardrobe rotation.

5.0 out of 5 stars Dude! This is what I call a Lightweight Jacket! But its cool enough for late Summer!
Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2024
Color: GreySize: X-LargeVine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
It doesn't say or even hint at being a lightweight jacket, but it truly is. In the end, this shirt will be worn when the temperature is between 48 and 69 degrees (9 to 20.5 Celsius). The cotton threading is dense, like an 1500 thread count mattress sheet. Already super soft, this shirt will soften up even more with time or environment. Well constructed, every cuff, button and collar are made of heavy duty stitches, something that promises to keep its shape and durability for decades. The vendor, Coofandy, has a flawless reputation for customer issues. They always respond immediately, and will resolve any issue with kindness and replacement. But you will not need them. They know the garment business better than anyone, except their own employees!

R.B.
5.0 out of 5 stars Nice Cool Weather Shirt
Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2024
Color: WhiteSize: X-LargeVine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
The COOFANDY Long Sleeve shirt comes vacuum packed and, as a result, has many wrinkles after removing it from the package.

I tried it on immediately and an XL fit me how I like: a little loose overall, but with a good sleeve length and room through the shoulders. I am 6'1" and 210lb for reference.

After a quick steaming, all the wrinkles from packaging came right out.

This is a very heavy (thick) shirt best suited to cooler season use. Its definitely not a summer shirt. Otherwise, the material and construction both seem high quality. I will be using the COOLFANDY as a casual shirt while at home in the cooler months, and as a formal shirt while traveling.
